data.title: Fast, friendly, just what you expect
data.text: The people do their job & are happy to do it.  The holiday specials really are special.  I can't wait to return.

data.title: Dirty
data.text: By Starbucks standards, this is not the best.  I visit quite a few different ones, this store surely represents the area.

data.title: Great store, bad parking
data.text: It's always a pleasure to stop at this store, but parking is a nightmare.  The staff has been working at this store for quite a while and are personable and friendly.

data.title: Very nice atmosphere with friendly staff
data.text: We ducked in this starbucks when it started to rain myself and family felt very relaxed in our environment with our lovely made drink's. We had seats was great to rest our tired legs. As we sat there we noticed how happy all the staff seemed to be with each other and customers it was lovely to see and made us feel happy that *Disney feeling* 😊

data.title: Inside the Target
data.text: Where I'm from you swing a cat and hit a coffee shop, not so much in the "World". Had to drive a few miles, yes miles to get an espresso drink! What?

data.title: This is my favorite Starbucks!
data.text: It's very busy at coffee-break time, plus you have the awesome art collection of the Grand Bohemian Hotel to enjoy. Don't try to park (unless you're staying at the Hotel): if you're driving, head farther south on Orange Ave to one of the few Starbucks with a drive-through (2453 S Orange Ave, Orlando, FL 32801).

data.title: Excelente servicio
data.text:
The baristas did a great job my drink was make it right & they give me sample odd others drinks 
Never try it before thanks guys

data.title: Best Pumpkin Spice Latte
data.text: I ordered a Pumpkin Spice Latte and it was delicious.  The whipped cream topped it off.  It's a shame they don't have this flavor year round.

data.title: Great Staff
data.text: I visit this Starbucks while travelling each year and have always had great customer service and prompt

data.title: Get's me going in the morning
data.text: Not far from my hotel and I love my Starbucks in the morning when I am on the road. Toasted bagel with creme cheese and a tall late. Good stuff.

data.title: Clean, timely, and accurate
data.text:
Easy to recommend this Starbucks location if in the Downtown Orlando area. It is part of the Grand Bohemian Hotel complex, so operates a bit different than some franchises.
My order was prompt and totally accurate on this Saturday afternoon. And the place is kept quite clean, which is often a challenge at other locations.

data.title: Worst Service
data.text: I had the most disenchanted barista in the world.   I'm a big Starbucks lover and I never encountered such awful attitude at any other location.   It was as though she was having a bad day, and taking it out on the customer.   My Frappuccinos were fine but no whip cream.  Isn't that the standard?  Or not in Orlando?

data.title: Enjoy the artwork while you caffinate
data.text:
Enjoyable Sunday morning visit for breakfast after a walk.

Pleasant staff, standard coffee and great artwork to view while you drink.

Part of the Grand Bohemian hotel.

data.title: Good Starbucks but a hotel contract
data.text: They will not honor rewards because they claim they are a hotel restaurant. Seems odd since they take the Starbucks app and the employees seem to be Starbucks employees.

data.title: Quality Assured
data.text: Wherever and whenever, Starbucks delivers. Always good coffee and many other drinks, plus fresh baked goods. Reasonable prices.

data.title: Quick, friendly service
data.text: All familiar Starbucks fare along with the various snacks.  Since I was visiting 0530, only a handful of people were in line.  I was greeted when walking in, ordered my food/drink and was out within 5 minutes.  This is a small Starbucks compared to others that I have visited, but provided all the same amenities.  Good for a quick breakfast sandwich and a hot coffee.

data.title: It's Starbucks
data.text: Late night stop! It was great that they were open late.  Our drinks were made well and the staff was very friendly.  Facilities were clean.

data.title: Early morning coffee
data.text: My 12-year-old son and I visited Starbucks many mornings before we took off to the local attractions. They were opened early which was great for us to get our day started. They have lots of food items, but most importantly they had the souvenier coffee mug with "Orlando" on it!

data.title: Its Starbucks
data.text: Nice option for a coffee right in the hotel, Place was clean, staff OK, not over the top friendly, otherwise a Starbucks!

data.title: Perfect location if you are staying at the Grand Bohemian
data.text: Perfect location if you are staying at the Grand Bohemian. All the customer service and selection we have come to expect from Starbucks. Open early.
